'From Squeak2.9alpha of 13 June 2000 [latest update: #2988] on 26 November 2000 at 9:46:46 am'!"Change Set:		251FindBtwSubStrsComment-dewDate:			15 November 2000Author:			Doug WayAdds a better comment to String>>findBetweenSubStrs: to make the behavior more clear."!!String methodsFor: 'accessing' stamp: 'dew 11/15/2000 15:02'!findBetweenSubStrs: delimiters	"Answer the collection of String tokens that result from parsing self.  Tokens are separated by 'delimiters', which can be a collection of Strings, or a collection of Characters.  Several delimiters in a row are considered as just one separation."	| tokens keyStart keyStop |	tokens _ OrderedCollection new.	keyStop _ 1.	[keyStop <= self size] whileTrue:		[keyStart _ self skipAnySubStr: delimiters startingAt: keyStop.		keyStop _ self findAnySubStr: delimiters startingAt: keyStart.		keyStart < keyStop			ifTrue: [tokens add: (self copyFrom: keyStart to: (keyStop - 1))]].	^tokens! !